$\because$
$$
\begin{array}{ll}
\because & \Delta H=\Delta U+\Delta(P V) \\
\text { or } & \Delta H=\Delta U+V \Delta P \\
\text { or } & \Delta U=\Delta H-V \Delta P
\end{array}
$$
Given that, $\Delta H=-560 \mathrm{~kJ}$
$$
\Delta P=40-70=-30 \mathrm{~atm}
$$

$$
\begin{array}{rlrl} 
& \therefore & V \Delta P & =1 \mathrm{~L} \times-30 \mathrm{~atm}=-30 \mathrm{~L} \text { atom } \\
& & 1 \mathrm{~L} \text {-atom } & =0.1 \mathrm{~kJ} \\
\therefore & V \Delta P & =-30 \times 0.1 \mathrm{~kJ} \\
\therefore & \Delta U & =-560-(-30 \times 0.1)=-557 \mathrm{~kJ}
\end{array}
$$
